    "title": "Recursive Spawning: Hierarchical Agent Lifecycle Management in Bounded Systems",
    "publication_date": "2026-04-24",
    "description": "Recursive Spawning defines the formal lifecycle management protocol for hierarchical multi-agent systems operating under bounded cognitive and physical constraints. We specify the recursive agent spawning semantics, hierarchical termination conditions, resource-bounded delegation, and cross-tier coordination patterns that ensure all agent activities remain within provably-enforced operational bounds. This paper formalizes the interaction patterns, role definition languages, and escalation protocols for large-scale deterministic agent deployments.",
